<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-21T09:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-21T09:16:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/570</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-21T16:00:00+01:44">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 22, 2:45 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_BT1">Talaat Bey</persName> and President of
                            Chamber are here to induce Roumania to join Turkey in favor of Austria
                            and Germany. It seems unlikely that Roumania will join Turkey as
                            Roumania evinced she is strong enough to act independently.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>